data.text:
Elizabeth of Ingoldisthorpe (24 June 1503 - 4 May 1547), also known as Elizabeth Dersingham, was a merchant's daughter who married Joel of Genovia and became Princess of Genovia. She came from the noble merchant family of Dersingham, who owned neighbouring villages Ingoldisthorpe and Dersingham.
